obo:GO_0098978  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4989  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4: Neo1 binds in trans to Cbln4/Nrxn1α-SS4+ complexes, forming bona fide adhesion complexes.\n\nFigure 2: Cbln4 deletion in the EC selectively blocks LTP at EC→DG synapses. (EC = entorhinal cortex, DG = dentate gyrus).\n\nFigure 5: Postsynaptic deletion of Neo1 in the DG severely impaired LTP in EC→DG synapses of both MPP (Fig. 5 E-G) and LPP connections (Fig. 5 H-J), similar to the presynaptic deletion of Cbln4 in the EC (Fig. 1).\n\nAuthors conclude that \"binding of cerebellin-4 (Cbln4), a secreted ligand of presynaptic neurexin adhesion molecules, to neogenin-1, a postsynaptic surface protein known as a developmental netrin receptor, is essential for normal LTP at entorhinal cortex→dentate gyrus synapses in mice. Cbln4 and neogenin-1 are dispensable for basal synaptic transmission and not involved in establishing synaptic connections as such.\". Experimental description: Supplementary M&M: \"All mouse experiments were performed in accordance with protocols approved by the Administrative Panel on Laboratory Animal Care (APLAC) at Stanford University. Cbln4 and Neo1 conditional KO (cKO) mice were previously described (PMID: 27143755, PMID: 28714144). Neo1 cKO mice have LoxP sites flanking the exon 1 of Neo1 gene. Wild type CD-1 mice were obtained from Charles River Laboratories.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4989" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

